Ad Text:
Build Technology That Transforms Healthcare
About us

At Seer, we believe technology can transform healthcare for the better. We design and build neurological monitoring devices that reimagine how and where care is delivered, putting patients first and enabling clinicians to act faster with better data.

By making home-based neurological monitoring accessible at scale, we are helping to relieve pressure on overburdened healthcare systems, accelerate diagnosis and treatment, and support better outcomes for people living with epilepsy and other neurological conditions.

Headquartered in Melbourne, Australia, our team includes over 20 engineers working across hardware, software and data science to push the boundaries of what is possible in medtech.

About the Role

We’re looking for a Graduate Machine Learning Engineer to contribute to the research and development of AI models used to interpret neurological signals and support clinical decision-making.

This role is focused on training and evaluating deep learning models for EEG, ECG, and video data, exploring new approaches to feature extraction, classification, and representation learning. You’ll assist with experiments, benchmarking, and data preparation, helping advance Seer’s AI research capability and contributing to publications, patents, and regulatory submissions.

Working closely with experienced ML engineers and data scientists, you’ll gain exposure to large-scale medical datasets, cutting-edge architectures, and the practical application of machine learning to real patient data.

This position is ideal for a graduate with strong analytical skills, curiosity about neuroscience and healthcare, and a passion for solving complex problems through ML research.

Key Responsibilities

Assist in the design, training, and evaluation of deep learning models for EEG, ECG, and video data.

Develop, document, and maintain ML training and inference using Python and PyTorch framework.

Support internal experiments on feature extraction, model interpretability, and algorithm robustness.

Collaborate with cloud engineers to develop cloud-based inference pipelines and deploy trained models into Seer Cloud infrastructure.

Write clean, maintainable code with testing and validation in mind.

Assist with documentation to support IEC 62304 software development and FDA submission requirements.

Participate in code reviews, sprint planning, and technical knowledge-sharing sessions.

Stay current with ML research and tools relevant to time-series, biomedical signal processing, and computer vision.


Education Requirements

Bachelor’s degree (or higher) in Computer Science, Engineering, Mathematics, Physics, or a related field.

Coursework or demonstrated experience in machine learning, data science, or applied statistics.




Experience Requirements

Practical experience with machine learning model development (academic, internship, or project-based).

Familiarity with deep learning frameworks such as PyTorch or TensorFlow.
Exposure to Python-based data ecosystems (NumPy, Pandas, scikit-learn).

Understanding of software development workflows using Git.

Experience working with real-world datasets (especially large or noisy ones) is advantageous.

Previous exposure to healthcare, neuroscience, or medical imaging data is desirable but not required.

What Makes This Special

Real Impact: Your code will be used in hospitals worldwide, directly improving patient care and clinical decision-making for epilepsy diagnosis.

Unique Experience: Gain invaluable exposure to medical device development, FDA approval processes, and regulated healthcare technology.

Cross-Functional Collaboration: Work alongside hardware teams, testers, and project managers in a multi-talented environment where quality and compliance are paramount.

Technical Growth: Build to the highest standards with emphasis on thorough testing, documentation, and regulatory compliance.

Benefits

Mission-Driven Work: Be part of technology that directly improves patient outcomes and clinical workflows in real hospital settings.

Professional Growth: Gain unique experience in regulated medical device development, FDA processes, and healthcare technology.

Flexible Working: Melbourne-based with remote options for the right candidate in AEST timezone. Flexible hours and work-from-home arrangements.

Competitive Package: Attractive salary package commensurate with experience.

Collaborative Culture: Work with a multi-talented team of engineers, testers, project managers, and hardware specialists.

Learning Opportunities: Annual learning & development budget and exposure to cutting-edge medical technology.

Ready to Make a Difference?

If building technology that transforms healthcare gets you excited, we'd love to hear from you!

Even if you don't meet 100% of the requirements listed above, we still encourage you to apply. We're committed to building a diverse and inclusive workplace and welcome applications from all backgrounds.

How to Apply

Please include your resume and a short paragraph about yourself and why you’d like to work at Seer Medical.

Our Process:

Screening interview with our Engineering Manager

Interactive code review task with our Engineering Manager

Culture and technical fit interview with leadership team

We promise to be respectful of your time while being thorough in finding the right fit for our team.

Applications accepted from candidates based in Australia with full working rights. Shortlisted candidates will be contacted promptly.

About Fast Automation:

Fast Automation is a leading Robotics and Automation company dedicated to revolutionizing industries through innovative automation solutions. With a focus on cutting-edge technology and a commitment to excellence, we specialize in delivering customized automation systems to enhance productivity, efficiency, and safety for our clients across various sectors.

Responsibilities:

Design, develop, and implement control systems for robotic and automation solutions, ensuring optimal performance, reliability, and scalability.

Collaborate with cross-functional teams including mechanical engineers, software engineers, and project managers to integrate control systems into overall automation solutions.

Conduct thorough analysis and testing of control systems to identify and address potential issues, optimize performance, and ensure compliance with project requirements and industry standards.

Excellent problem-solving skills and the ability to analyze complex technical issues, develop innovative solutions, and troubleshoot control system problems effectively.

Exceptional communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to collaborate effectively with multidisciplinary teams and communicate technical concepts to non-technical stakeholders.

Proven leadership abilities, with experience in mentoring junior engineers and leading control system design projects from concept to completion.

Requirements:

Bachelor's degree or higher in Electrical Engineering, Mechatronics, or a related field.

Proven experience (minimum 5 years) in designing, developing, and implementing control systems for robotics and automation applications, with expertise in Siemens and Rockwell PLC programming.

Strong proficiency in PLC programming, particularly with Siemens (e.g., SIMATIC S7, TIA Portal) and Rockwell (e.g., ControlLogix, Studio 5000) platforms, including programming logic, motion control, and communication protocols.

Thorough understanding of control systems and ability to interpret and modify electrical drawings.

Excellent problem-solving skills and the ability to analyze complex technical issues, develop innovative solutions, and troubleshoot control system problems effectively.

Exceptional communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to collaborate effectively with multidisciplinary teams and communicate technical concepts to non-technical stakeholders.

Proven leadership abilities, with experience in mentoring junior engineers and leading control system design projects from concept to completion.

Why Join Fast Automation?

Opportunity to work on cutting-edge projects at the forefront of robotics and automation technology.

Collaborative and innovative work environment that fosters creativity, learning, and professional growth.

Competitive salary and benefits package, including opportunities for career advancement and skill development.

Chance to make a meaningful impact by contributing to solutions that drive efficiency, productivity, and safety across various industries.

Fast Automation is an equal-opportunity employer committed to diversity and inclusion in the workplace. We welcome applications from individuals of all backgrounds and experiences.

If you are passionate about robotics, automation, and pushing the boundaries of technology, we encourage you to apply for this exciting opportunity to join our team!

Work with cutting edge AI technology, making the world a safer and more secure place. DroneShield (ASX:DRO) offers an opportunity to solve some of world’s most challenging technical problems in the rapidly growing counterdrone sector. Our customers are militaries, government agencies, airports, critical infrastructure, law enforcement and many others.




With one of the largest listed defence company market capitalisations in Australia, part of the ASX200 index, and having raised approximately $250m in 2024 alone, DroneShield is undergoing hypergrowth stage, fuelled by rapidly increasing use of drones for nefarious applications, from battlefield, to terrorism, to contraband delivery and commercial espionage.




This role is in the DroneShield Sydney headquarters in Sydney CBD. There are approximately 380 staff based in the 4,000sqm facility today, scheduled to grow to approximately 500 staff by end of 2026. Overseas on the ground presence includes Virginia (USA), Netherlands, Denmark, Mexico and Dubai, as well as distributors in over 70 countries globally.







About the role

DroneShield is seeking an Embedded Systems Engineer to join the Sydney team. The primary focus of this role is to develop and maintain embedded sensor systems, integrating software, electronics, and mechanical components. You will collaborate closely with ML/AI, Data Science, Embedded, RF, and infrastructure teams to innovate and enhance DroneShield’s world-leading RF detection technology.




Responsibilities, Duties and Expectations 

Design, develop, and implement embedded Linux-based systems, combining software, electronics, and mechanical components.
Ensure systems are robust, high-performing, and reliable on resource-constrained targets.
Collaborate with multidisciplinary teams to meet technical, operational, and business requirements.
Support end-to-end system operation, including sensing, control, and actuation components.
Develop and maintain technical documentation covering software modules, hardware interfaces, and overall system behaviour.
Contribute to system integration and testing, ensuring seamless interaction between mechanical, electrical, and software components.

Qualifications, Experience and Skills 

Strong experience in embedded software development (C/C++, Python, or similar).
Familiarity with Linux-based embedded systems.
Understanding of electronics and mechanical system integration.
Exposure to RF, sensor, or mechatronic systems is a plus.
Ability to work collaboratively across multidisciplinary teams.




Note for recruitment agencies: We do not accept unsolicited candidates from external recruiters unless specifically instructed.

Your Impact

As a Control & Automation Engineer you’ll play a key role in keeping our packaging operations running safely and efficiently at our Tullamarine site. You’ll take ownership of electrical and automation systems across the site, from PLCs and SCADA to coders, robotics, servo motion and line control systems. Working alongside Reliability and Engineering teams, you’ll troubleshoot complex issues, drive system improvements, and support new projects and upgrades that lift plant performance.

 

Key Responsibilities

Maintain and optimise control and automation systems, including PLCs, SCADA, robotics, servo and vision systems.
Ensure all electrical systems meet Australian Standards and site safety requirements.
Provide hands-on support for breakdown investigations and troubleshooting across legacy and modern equipment.
Develop, implement and continuously improve maintenance and calibration plans.
Support commissioning and implementation of new projects and technologies.
Contribute to site-wide automation standards, EOL (End-of-Life) strategies and continuous improvement initiatives.
Collaborate cross-functionally with Production, Maintenance, and Engineering teams to deliver system reliability and uptime.

 

About You

A tertiary qualification in Electrical, Mechatronics or Control Systems Engineering
5+ years’ experience in a maintenance, automation or reliability role within FMCG, chemical or pharmaceutical manufacturing.
Strong knowledge of Australian electrical standards and safety systems.
Proven experience with PLCs, SCADA, and automation troubleshooting (Siemens / Allen-Bradley highly regarded).
Hands-on, proactive problem-solver who thrives in fast-paced, legacy plant environments.
Strong communicator and collaborator with a continuous improvement mindset.
Leadership skills to support and mentor others as the function grows.

 

Why Asahi Beverages?


At Asahi Beverages, we're passionate about crafting more than just drinks - we craft moments of connection, celebration, and shared enjoyment. We bring together a diverse portfolio of iconic beverage brands, a commitment to quality, and a drive to constantly innovate.  Headquartered in Melbourne and with facilities right across Australia and New Zealand, you’ll find Asahi is a place where talent is nurtured, and ambition is rewarded. If you’re ready to toast your future, we’re ready to meet you.

Job Title: Lead Data Scientist / Lead AI Engineer - GenAI - Sydney
Ad Text:
The Opportunity

Our client is a high-growth scale-up on a mission to expand and make an impact through the delivery of innovative AI and automation solutions.

They’re seeking a Lead Data Scientist and a Lead AI Engineer to lead the design, engineering and delivery of GenAI solutions across a broad range of enterprise projects. This includes building AI agents, architecting end-to-end machine learning systems, and guiding strategic AI readiness consulting engagements. You'll act as a technical lead, people manager, and client advisor - playing a pivotal role in shaping how the business scales its AI capabilities.

The role is paying $160-180K + Super +10% Bonus + ESOP with a hybrid work environment (3-4 days a week in Sydney CBD office). 

The ideal candidate is commercially minded, technically excellent, and deeply curious about the evolving AI landscape, especially Generative AI. Whether you've had hands-on GenAI experience or are actively exploring it in your own time, you'll need to demonstrate the ability to turn ideas into real-world, high-impact solutions.
  
Key Responsibilities

Lead complex GenAI and data science projects from discovery to production
Mentor and grow a small team of data scientists and engineers
Engage with clients as a trusted technical advisor - shaping roadmaps, presenting solutions, and influencing senior stakeholders
Architect AI systems and integrate models, workflows, and APIs into scalable solutions
Contribute to product strategy by feeding back market insights and customer needs
Collaborate cross-functionally with product, marketing, and delivery teams
Stay ahead of the curve on new AI tools, trends, and methods - especially GenAI
  
What You’ll Bring

7+ years of experience in data science, with solid machine learning and AI engineering skills
Confident in client-facing roles - leading workshops, scoping engagements, and delivering design architecture proposals and technical presentations
Deep interest in Generative AI and emerging technologies
Tech/team leadership experience in data science
Retail analytics experience is a bonus
Coding experience with Python and familiarity with modern AI stacks (e.g. LangChain, Hugging Face, TensorFlow, PyTorch)
Experience building scalable data pipelines and working with cloud-native tools (e.g. Snowflake, dbt, Airflow)
A start-up / scale-up mindset: adaptable, proactive, commercially driven, and excited to shape something from the ground up
 
Why Join?

This is a rare chance to join an emerging player in the AI space and shape its technical direction at a foundational level. You’ll work on exciting, future-focused projects with a passionate, collaborative team and have a real voice in how the business evolves.

Start Date: 19 January 2026

Primary Purpose

Support the Department’s ICT Operations Branch by delivering advanced automation, virtualisation, and infrastructure management services. This role ensures stable, secure, and scalable IT environments across the department’s data centres, underpinning critical systems and ministerial operations.

Maintain VMware vSphere and Cloud Foundation environments (rack-mounted and blade servers)
Develop and automate infrastructure provisioning and configuration processes using PowerShell, PowerCLI, YAML, and JavaScript

Company Description

About SEEK

SEEK’s portfolio of diverse businesses make a positive impact on a truly global scale. Our purpose is to help people live more fulfilling and productive working lives and help organisations succeed. We create world-class technology solutions to connect more people to relevant employment, education, small business and volunteer opportunities. We have a culture of high-performance in our workplaces and celebrate the diversity of our employees who contribute to the success of our organisation.

Life at SEEK

SEEK’s purpose is at the centre of everything we do. Our SEEK, which defines the way we work, is all about what makes us unique and a little bit different. Passion, Team, Delivery and Future are our principles that drive innovation and creativity. SEEK strives to support employee wellbeing by providing an amazing experience at work which led us to being named AFR BOSS Top 10 Best Places to Work in Technology (2021-2024). We are proud to work in an environment that's inclusive where everyone's unique ideas, experiences and perspectives are valued.

Our award-winning head office in Cremorne (just a 4 min walk from Richmond station) provides an exceptional space to collaborate with colleagues. The building provides sweeping views of the city, a games area, sit and stand desks at every workstation, modern end-of-trip facilities and Thursday night drinks which gives our people an opportunity to connect in a social setting.

Job Description

The Team

The AI & Analytics Data Products team builds high-quality data assets that empower teams across SEEK Group to gain valuable insights and enhance experiences for both individuals and organisations.

This position will report to the Engineering Manager and be part of a team made up of senior and mid-level data engineers. The team collaborates closely with internal peers, including staff, senior, and mid-level data engineers; analytics engineers; data solution designers; and data tracking specialists.

About the role 

A Lead Data Engineer is a hands-on technical role, contributing to the build and operation of technical solutions, but has additional leadership responsibility for people management and delivery outcomes.

Responsibilities 

Technology

Hands-on development and operational support duties alongside other data engineers.
Ongoing ownership of solutions you build to ensure they remain fit for purpose, meet customer needs, meet technology health metrics, and align with architectural guidelines.

Delivery

Driving customer focus and engagement to ensure we are delivering outcomes for our customers.
Setting goals, prioritising, planning, as well as contributing to budgeting and resourcing
Lead delivery and operation of data products, along with the data processing pipelines and orchestration to deliver them.

People

Direct line management of a small team of engineers
Performance review and management of individuals.
Professional growth via coaching and mentoring.
Qualifications

Skills and experience 

Proven years of experience in Data Engineering, delivering scalable, reliable, and production-grade data solutions on cloud platforms
Deep expertise in big data processing frameworks, ideally Apache Spark on Databricks or AWS EMR. Solid experience of both batch and streaming data pipelines
Strong software engineering background, with solid practices in CI/CD, automated testing, and version control
Advanced proficiency in SQL and database design, with a strong focus on performance optimisation and data modelling
Proven track record in infrastructure ownership, including deployment, system administration, monitoring, and operations (with a DevOps mindset)
Strong experience in coding with Python. Good experience with Scala is a bonus.
Solid experience with Cloud Data Warehouse like Databricks, Snowflake or Big Query
Deep understanding of AWS services, with a focus on Big Data technologies such as EMR, Athena, Glue, and S3, as well as experience with IAM, Cloudformation, CDK, Lambda, SNS, SQS, SSM
Extensive background in supporting BI, Analytics, Data Science, and AI/ML initiatives
With at least 3+ years of experience in leading and mentoring team members, contributing to their technical growth and fostering a collaborative team culture
Demonstrated ability to own and deliver end-to-end solutions using Agile methodologies —driving initiative planning, iterative solution design, and stakeholder engagement to ensure alignment and value delivery
Additional Information

Permanent Perks

Annual Performance Bonus Plan
Support of flexible working, including a mix of office and work from home days depending on your role.
Paid and unpaid leave benefits including Personal Flexi Days and Volunteer Days, as well as the opportunity to purchase additional leave
Support for parents with 14 weeks paid primary carers leave and 2 weeks paid leave for partners

If you’re passionate about turning cutting-edge AI ideas into commercial impact, this is the role to shape an organisations future from the inside.

Working closely with business leaders, engineers, and data teams, you’ll identify opportunities where AI can drive efficiency, enhance customer outcomes, and open up new possibilities for growth.

What You’ll Be Doing:

About You:

Demonstrated experience leading enterprise-level AI initiatives or transformations.
Strong technical grounding in AI/ML frameworks, LLMs, intelligent agents, and automation technologies.
The ability to translate complex technical concepts into clear business outcomes.
Leadership experience with direct reports within cross-functional environments where innovation and governance go hand-in-hand.
A curious mindset and passion for driving continuous improvement.

About Us

We are a technology-driven company specialising in advanced photoluminescence imaging and spectroscopy systems for photovoltaic cell and wafer inspection. Our systems are used globally in research and manufacturing environments, combining precision hardware with intelligent software.

The Role

We are seeking an experienced Software Engineer with strong LabVIEW expertise to lead development and enhancement of our hardware control, vision acquisition, and imaging workflows. You will design, implement, and maintain robust LabVIEW applications for device control, data acquisition, and image processing. Expertise in LabVIEW and the Actor Framework is a strong advantage.

While the primary focus is LabVIEW, familiarity with Python is a plus for future-related projects (e.g., analytics services, tooling, or potential module porting).

Key Responsibilities

Lead development and maintenance of a LabVIEW (Actor Framework) application for hardware control and imaging

Implement and optimize image acquisition, processing, and analysis pipelines in LabVIEW (and integrate with vision libraries where appropriate)

Design and implement a modular backend for device control and data acquisition

Integrate hardware devices such as cameras, lasers, motors, PLCs, and spectrometers

Interface with communication protocols including RS232, RS485, Ethernet/IP, USB3, and GigE Vision

Collaborate with the wider team to ensure reliable end-to-end system performance and a responsive user experience.

Document the system architecture and provide training/handover support where needed

Required Skills & Experience

5+ years of professional software development experience

5+ years hands-on experience with LabVIEW for hardware control, data acquisition, and imaging

Strong understanding of LabVIEW Actor Framework and modular application design

Proven experience integrating industrial hardware and communication protocols (RS232/RS485/Ethernet/IP/USB3/GigE Vision)

Solid grasp of image acquisition/processing concepts in LabVIEW (e.g., NI Vision/IMAQ)

Strong architecture skills and software engineering best practices

Comfortable in a Linux and Windows mixed development environment

Excellent debugging, testing (including hardware-in-the-loop), and documentation skills

Desirable

Background in scientific instrumentation, automation, or laboratory control systems

Knowledge of photovoltaic technologies or optical imaging systems

Experience developing frontend applications using HTML5, CSS, JavaScript, and frameworks such as React or Vue.js

Familiarity with containerization (Docker), CI/CD, or real-time data processing pipelines

Strong experience with Python in hardware control or instrumentation environments

Familiarity with OpenCV or other image analysis frameworks

Experience working with REST APIs, messaging systems (e.g. ZeroMQ, MQTT), or similar

What We Offer

Opportunity to work on cutting-edge photonics and imaging systems

Collaborative and innovative engineering environment

Flexible contract arrangements (6 or 12 months to start, with potential for extension)

Relocation assistance for the right candidate

LMS Energy is Australia’s largest emissions reducer and the national leader in biogas-to-energy and solar on landfill. LMS requires the services of a full-time or part-time Control Systems Engineer in Prospect, South Australia. 

As a key member of our team, you'll work across the full lifecycle of control systems for complex and innovative bioenergy projects. From initial design to commissioning, you'll contribute technical expertise and help shape systems that support LMS' growing portfolio of Agwaste, landfill gas and renewable energy assets. The role offers hands-on experience across multiple platforms, collaboration with multidisciplinary teams, and potential opportunities for project support overseas. 

Why LMS Energy?

Be a part of an inclusive team, where everything we do is inspired by our vision to be the leading bioenergy and methane abatement company, powering the circular economy. Our people are supported by management with an open-door policy, while training and development opportunities means we enjoy an unrivalled level of personal progression and growth. At LMS, we have an average staff tenure of five years. In our Engagement Survey for 2024, 94% of employees either agreed or strongly agreed that they would recommend LMS as a place to work. Why? We truly value our people. Without our people, we would not be the great business we are today!

Our commitment to you

Health and wellbeing options, including the opportunity to work from home, flexible start and finish times, a weekly wellbeing hour and access to our holistic Employee Assistance Program (EAP). 
Learning and development in supportive team environment with professional, safety and technical training opportunities and growth pathways. 
Community impact with participation in various charitable activities and volunteering opportunities using a "Give Back Day". 
Diversity, equity and inclusion committee and focus groups, ensuring a workplace where every individual feels valued, included and empowered. 
Leave entitlements, including prorated long-service leave, study leave and employer-paid parental leave. 
Rewards and recognition for length of service and cultural and safety excellence. 

Responsibilities:

Design, program and commission automation and control systems using Allen-Bradley Logix processors and Citect SCADA

Maintain and optimise control systems across platforms including Siemens S7, Red Lion, and legacy Allen-Bradley (Logix and SLC500)

Develop and manage communication protocols such as Modbus TCP/RTU, HART, CANbus, and associated HMI systems

Apply electrical engineering knowledge to power distribution, control schematics, protection systems, VFD configuration, and network communications

Prepare and maintain documentation including I/O lists, specifications, control philosophies, and scopes of work

Provide technical support to operations including troubleshooting, fault finding, and driving continuous improvement

Coordinate and oversee contractors during installation and commissioning to ensure quality, compliance, and safety

Requirements:

A bachelor's degree in a relevant engineering field or equivalent technical experience 

A minimum of 5+ years of hands-on experience in developing, integrating, testing and commissioning PLC-based automation and control systems 

Proficient with Rockwell Automation Studio5000 / RSLogix500 software and Citect SCADA 

Experience in FAT and SAT  

Strong technical skills in PLC and RTU programming  

Effective organisational and time management capabilities with a keen focus on detail 

Australian Drivers Licence 

Uphold LMS’ company values and culture 

Employment is conditional upon a pre-employment medical and entitlement to work in Australia. Some roles require up-to date vaccinations records. 

Please email applications to employment@lms.com.au, quoting job reference ENGN-043-311025. 
 

We are continuously searching for passionate individuals that value the environment, have a caring outlook, and want to work towards a brighter future. If this sounds like you, please click apply, we’d love to hear from you! Check out our website to learn more about what we do https://www.lms.com.au/ .

Job Title: Senior Manager - AI Strategy and Metrics
Ad Text:
Senior Manager - AI Strategy and Metrics

AI-powered Automation COO | Commonwealth Bank


If you're inspired by the potential of AI and excited to shape the future of intelligent operations, this is your opportunity to make a meaningful impact. Together, we'll advance LLM and ML-powered automation across the COO.

Your Impact:

Join CommBank's pioneering AI-powered Automation COO Crew, a cross-functional team embedded in CTO and aligned with COO priorities. We're building secure, scalable, and intelligent automation solutions using LLMs and machine learning to solve real operational pain points-from customer offboarding to document triage and home loan discharge.

As Senior Manager - AI Strategy and Metrics, you'll lead the strategic and analytical backbone of this transformation. Your work will define how we measure success, guide investment, and ensure every AI solution delivers tangible business value.

You'll work closely with the Crew Lead and Distinguished Engineer to ensure strategy and metrics are grounded in technical excellence and aligned with enterprise engineering standards.

What You'll Do:


Design and Optimise AI Metrics: Lead the development and continuous improvement of performance metrics for LLM and ML-powered agents operating in production. This includes tracking both quantity (e.g. number of agents deployed, cases handled) and quantitative impact (e.g. turnaround time, error reduction, cost efficiency).

Strategic Recommendations: Provide high-level strategic and metrics recommendations to guide the evolution of AI-powered automation across COO domains.

Partner with COO Stakeholders: Collaborate closely with business leaders across the COO to ensure automation metrics and strategy are aligned with operational priorities and transformation goals.

Shape the Strategy: Define and evolve the AI roadmap for automation, ensuring alignment with enterprise platforms and engineering standards.

Measure What Matters: Establish performance frameworks to track impact across speed, accuracy, resilience, and business value.

Drive Data-Driven Decisions: Use real-world data to inform experimentation, benchmark impact, and guide prioritisation.

Lead Governance & Alignment: Coordinate quarterly steering reviews with CTO and COO stakeholders, ensuring transparency and strategic alignment.

Support Investment Cases: Quantify the value of AI-powered automation and support funding decisions with clear, data-backed outcomes.

Promote Visibility: Elevate the strategy through executive dashboards, showcases, and reporting that inspire and inform.

What You'll Measure:

You'll help shape and optimise high-level metrics across four key dimensions:


Observability & Operational Health: Monitor system uptime, integration stability, and performance indicators to ensure resilient and available AI agents.

AI Performance & Quality: Track accuracy, usefulness, and failure patterns using a blend of automated and human-in-the-loop evaluations.

Business Efficiency & Cost Impact: Quantify turnaround time improvements, cost per case, and scalability benefits to demonstrate ROI.

Strategic Value & Resilience: Measure adaptability, SLA adherence, and operational coverage to position AI as a long-term enabler for growth.

What You Bring:


Proven experience in AI strategy, analytics, or performance management in large-scale tech or operations environments.

Strong understanding of LLMs, ML Ops, and intelligent automation principles.

Ability to translate technical outcomes into business value for senior stakeholders.

Experience leading cross-functional initiatives across product, engineering, and business teams.

Familiarity with Agile delivery, experimentation models, and continuous improvement.

Exceptional communication and storytelling skills, with a track record of executive-level influence.

Why Join Us:

At CommBank, we're not just adopting AI-we're redefining how operations work. You'll be part of a high-impact crew that acts as a force-multiplier for operations, with the backing of CTO and COO leadership. Our mission is bold, our roadmap is clear, and our impact is measurable.

We celebrate diversity, encourage bold thinking, and support flexible working. If you're excited by this opportunity but don't tick every box, we still want to hear from you.


Whether you're passionate about customer service, driven by data, or called by creativity, a career here is for you.

Our people bring their diverse backgrounds and unique perspectives to build a respectful, inclusive and flexible workplace. We are working hard to build a team of people who represent the rich diversity of our customers and communities. If you're excited about this opportunity but you don't meet every single requirement, or your experience doesn't align perfectly, we still want to encourage you to apply. You may just be the perfect candidate for this opportunity or another within CommBank.

At CommBank we will inspire you with work that makes a difference, surround you with talented people that respect and value each other, and empower you to grow professionally and personally. Most of all, making a positive impact for customers, communities and each other is part of our every day.

We're determined to make a real difference for Australia's first peoples. We encourage all interested applicants to apply. If you're already part of the Commonwealth Bank Group (including Bankwest), you'll need to apply through Sidekick to submit a valid application. We're keen to support you with the next step in your career.

Macquarie University is seeking a talented and experienced Senior Digital Engineer to guide and support the delivery of semiconductor and technology projects. This is a fabulous opportunity to join the newly established Silicon Platforms Lab (SiPLab) within the Faculty of Science and Engineering at Macquarie University.

In this role, you will enhance both your skills and the reputation of the SiP Lab team. You will collaborate with a dynamic digital team in developing advanced wireless and sensing hardware platforms, overseeing the delivery of semiconductor and technology projects.

If you're passionate about making an impact and driving innovation in semiconductor research, this could be the opportunity for you? Apply now to begin your journey with Macquarie SiP team.

What you'll do as a Senior Digital Engineer in the SiP Lab

Provide guidance and support to the SiP Lab project team ensuring that project deliverable milestones are met within timeframes and budget.
Actively contribute to the development of engineering designs from concept to production including design, manufacturing, testing, pre-production validation and documentation.
Innovate and push the state-of-the-art in the context of engineering in industry - specific areas of leadership include Systems design, Hardware and IC design, IC packaging and assembly, Silicon measurement, and EDA/CAD tools.
Develop and review concepts, system and subsystem level designs for semiconductor projects within the workgroup area of expertise.
Write and review documentation for project reviews.
Develop, review, and analyse system requirements, the flow-down of these requirements from system to sub-system levels, and the systems modelling, and analysis required for requirements verification.
Contribute to the management and administering of the project budget.

About Us

The Faculty of Scienceand Engineering offers both undergraduate and postgraduate Degree programs across a diverse range of disciplines. The Faculty is also home to a number of world-class research centres. The Faculty continues to grow links with industry by building partnerships with commercial, government, cultural and professional organisations.

The SiP Lab is an advanced silicon chip design lab with advanced silicon system-on-chip (SoC) / system-in-package (SiP) capabilities. The research focuses on key semiconductor industry trends in communications and sensing, as well as partnering with adjacent research teams across the Faculty of Science and Engineering and the wider University to integrate their own novel IP onto a silicon platform, with benefits anticipated in the fields of synthetic biology, photonics, and quantum technologies.

More details about our SiP Lab can be found at: https://www.mq.edu.au/faculty-of-science-and-engineering/our-research/silicon-platforms-lab

How to Apply

To be considered for this position, please apply online by submitting your CV and a separate document responding to the selection criteria below

Proven ability contributing to a digital team in developing advanced wireless and sensing hardware platforms.
Demonstrated experience in supervising the digital implementation of advanced DSP blocks on FPGA and ASIC platforms.
Strong background in supporting the design and modelling of digital signal processing blocks in FPGA and ASIC platforms.
Commitment to ensuring the quality of DSP development.
Experience and knowledge of MIMO, DPD, CFR, Equalization, DUC/DDC, and FFT.
Expertise in ensuring a rigorous system-level test and validation process through best practices in CI/CD regression testing.

This position requires criminal record checks.

Enquiries: Professor Michael Boers at m.boers@mq.edu.au

Salary package: from $122,628 to $136,449 per annum, plus 17% employer superannuation and annual leave loading. Additional market allowance may be available depending on candidate experience.

The successful candidate must be able to hold and maintain a 10A Defence Export Controls Permit under the Defence Trade Controls Act (2012), or be able to access an exemption.

Applications Close: 31st Oct 2025 at 11:59pm (AEST)

*** Applications will be reviewed as they are received, and we reserve the right to progress or decline an application prior to the application closing date. We also reserve the right to close the advertisement early if a sufficient number of qualified applicants is received.

Why work at Macquarie

We rank amongst the top employers in the Australian Workplace Employers Index, having recently earned a five-star rating in the QS World Rankings with the highest rating for employability.

Our prime location, we are walking distance from Macquarie University Metro Station and Macquarie Shopping Centre. Not only are we close, take a look at our benefits on offer:



17% Superannuation

Training and professional development

A Place Where You Belong

At Macquarie, we believe diversity makes us stronger, inclusion drives our success, and belonging inspires us to do our best work. We are proud to foster a community where different backgrounds, identities, and experiences are valued, and where our people are empowered to thrive through supportive leadership, shared responsibility, and a deep commitment to genuine care and respect for our community. Find out more about our vision for a truly inclusive workplace in our Diversity, Inclusion and Belonging Framework.

Flexible Work

At Macquarie, we believe by providing flexibility in when, where and how work is done, we can support our staff to manage their personal commitments, while optimising their work performance and contributions to the University. See how we lead in flexible work to enable an outcome focused and inclusive workplace. To learn more about our culture and hiring process, explore our Jobs at Macquarie page.

Johnson Controls is a global diversified technology and multi-industrial leader serving a wide range of customers in more than 150 countries. Our 135,000 employees create intelligent buildings, efficient energy solutions, integrated infrastructure and next generation transportation systems that work seamlessly together to deliver on the promise of smart cities and communities. We are seeking a highly motivated self-starter with a “can do” approach and solid embedded C software design and development skills to join our Traffic and Transportation division in the Traffic Product Development Team. This role is ideal for someone with a solid foundation in safety critical real time controls systems who thrives on providing innovative solutions for our customers.

In this role, you will be working very closely with a multidisciplinary engineering team in a hands-on role at Rydalmere. This is an exciting opportunity to highlight your software real time design and development skills.

If you’re passionate about delivering exceptional new and improved designs and want to be part of a business that values proactive thinking — this is the opportunity for you!

About this opportunity:

We need a Senior Embedded Software Engineer to perform the design and development of embedded control systems for Traffic Signal Controllers. This role requires expertise in safety-critical embedded software, digital hardware integration, and control systems design, with an emphasis on compliance with SIL2 (IEC 61508) safety standards.

The successful candidate will combine strong low-level C programming skills with the ability to understand and influence hardware design (primarily digital electronics), while ensuring fail-safe and reliable performance for Traffic Signal Controllers.

How you will do it:

Design and implement safety-critical embedded software for Traffic Signal Controllers in compliance with SIL2 (IEC 61508 / ISO 26262).

Develop and validate conflict monitoring, phase control, and lamp monitoring algorithms for Traffic Signal Controllers.

Collaborate with hardware engineers in the design of fault-tolerant digital interfaces (GPIO, latching outputs, watchdogs, memory functionality, reliable flash chip programming).

Lead system integration across MCUs, SoCs, and RTOSs

Develop and execute debug code to verify designs/ customer requirements.

Implement and maintain communication protocols (SCATS, NEMA TS2, ITS standards, CAN, Ethernet) for roadside devices and central system integration.

Develop web-based interfaces for local and remote-control functionality.

Ensure robust secure communications, OTA firmware updates, and diagnostics for long-term field deployments.

Participate in safety case documentation: hazard analysis, FMEA/FMELA, traceability, and compliance with certification bodies.

Mentor junior software engineers and perform peer reviews of designs and code.

Produce design, architecture, verification, validation and software release documentation.

What we look for:

Essential:

Proven experience (10 years+) developing embedded software for SIL2 (or higher) safety-critical systems, preferably in transportation, rail, or industrial control.

Strong C programming skills for MCUs and real-time operating systems, with demonstrable ability implementing algorithms and debugging hardware/ software interactions using oscilloscopes, logic analysers, and bus analysers.

Deep understanding of digital electronics and I/O design, including watchdogs, fail-safe states, redundancy, and EMC considerations.

Familiarity with protocols and standards in the traffic and transport domain (SCATS, NEMA TS2, ITS, CAN, Ethernet, Modbus, RS-485).

Hands-on experience with real-time simulation, and fault injection for validation of safety systems.

Contribution to safety case documentation and engagement with external certification authorities/auditors.

Demonstrated ability to integrate embedded Linux (desirable) for communications/ UI while keeping safety functions isolated on RT cores/ MCUs.

Desirable:

Experience with traffic control algorithms, conflict detection, phase timing, and intergreen intervals.

Experience in secure boot, OTA update frameworks (RAUC/OSTree), and cybersecurity for embedded systems.

Exposure to Yocto/Buildroot, RTOS (Micrium, FreeRTOS), or dual-core MCU + Linux SoC designs.

Prior work in roadside, rail, transport systems or medical fields with harsh environment constraints.

Only those candidates the Company (recruitment Agency Company) introduces to JCI by resumes on JCI’s Talent Acquisitions team’s explicit request will be deemed a candidate referred by the Company.

Please note pre-employment checks – including reference checks, medical, criminal record check, and drug & alcohol testing – will form part of the eligibility process.

Only applicants who have a current right to work in Australia will be considered.

Click on the APPLY button to submit your application in confidence.

AWS Data Engineer (Data Pipeline & Migration Focus)

The senior data engineer will establish and implement the data engineering capability on a new AWS-based data platform.
The engineer will design and build data pipelines, reporting solutions, and ETL processes, migrating data from legacy platforms (Omnia, Teradata) to strategic AWS-based data systems.

Core Responsibilities

Design, build, and maintain ETL/data pipelines using AWS native tools (Glue, Redshift, S3, Lambda, Step Functions).

Support data migration from Teradata/Omnia to AWS.

Develop and optimize Spark ETL jobs and data transformation logic.

Deliver reporting data sets and data models for analytics teams.

Collaborate with platform and analytics teams to ensure data reliability, scalability, and governance.

Evaluate and propose improvements in data engineering and pipeline design.

Key Requirements:

5-10 years' experience in data engineering, with hands-on experience in AWS.

Proven track record of building data pipelines and migrating from on-prem/legacy systems.

Strong SQL, Spark, and Python developer.

AWS Glue, Redshift, S3, Spark, PySpark, SQL, ETL orchestration.

Category:
Consultants (Information & Communication Technology)
Government - State (Government & Defence)
Ad Text:
What you'll do  

Manage the design, planning and implementation of technical solutions, ensuring alignment with best practice IM/ICT design and delivery frameworks.
Specifies and designs complex systems and recommends appropriate design standards, methods and tools, consistent with agreed enterprise and solution architectures and ensures effective application.
Maintains an in-depth knowledge of technical specialisms and provides expert advice regarding Identity and Access application.
Automating User Lifecycle Processes: Implementing solutions for user provisioning, modification, and deprovisioning to streamline identity workflows 
Ensuring Compliance: Maintaining alignment with organisational policies, security standards, and audit requirements 
Enterprise Integration: Designing and executing integrations between IAM systems and enterprise applications to support seamless access and data flow 
System Customization & Maintenance: Tailoring NetIQ IAM components to meet evolving business needs and ensuring ongoing system stability and performance 
This position demands a strong understanding of identity governance, access control, and enterprise architecture, along with the ability to collaborate across technical and business teams to deliver secure, scalable solutions. 
Manage the development, publication, implementation and compliance of all program/project(s) deliverables and related standards and procedures at an enterprise level.

About you  

We are searching for someone who has:

Experience in the design, publication, implementation, compliance and delivery of technical solutions in enterprise systems to industry best practice frameworks for large scale, complex IM/ICT program/project(s) with experience in some or all of the following hardware software: NetIQ Identity Manager driver development, Virtual Infrastructure, Windows, Unix and Linux Server Operating Environments, Cloud and Directory Services – Entra/AzureAD, eDirectory and ADFS, ServiceNow integration and PowerShell Scripting, preferably in the healthcare industry.  (SFIA Skill: ITMG: Level 5, HSIN: Level 4)
Experience designing systems and providing expert knowledge in relevant design standards, techniques and methods and tools for large scale complex organisations. (SFIA Skill: DESN: Level 4, METL: 5)
Demonstrated experience in the assessment, analysis, development, documentation and implementation planning of changes for large complex IM/ICT program/project(s). (SFIA Skill: CHMG: Level 4)
Demonstrated high level analytical, conceptual and problem solving skills with a proven record in the assessment and evaluation of technical requirements within a complex IM/ICT environment)

Why work with us?  

Work alongside passionate professionals in a supportive and inclusive environment that values people and prioritises employee success and wellbeing. 

Competitive salaries 

12.75% superannuation  
17.5% leave loading 

Employee wellbeing & development 

Access to 24/7 confidential employee support providers and counsellors including for immediate family members 
Additional flexibility to support your work life balance including access to generous leave entitlements, such as purchased leave, domestic violence leave, reproductive health leave, cultural leave, study and examination leave. 
Access to a variety of programs and initiatives to support training and career growth.  

Our commitment to equity, diversity and inclusion  

At Queensland Health, our work environment is inclusive and supportive, and we value our employees. We are an equal opportunity employer and encourage applications from people of all cultures, abilities and backgrounds.  

Our commitment to cultural safety, equity, diversity and inclusion means we understand some people may need changes to the recruitment process. If you need support during the recruitment process, such as meeting with the panel virtually instead of in person, please reach out to the hiring manager. We value diverse candidates and your need for adjustments will not affect our hiring decisions.

Job Description

Great humans needed. Combine the best of your ingenuity and Cloud technologies to build a better world and manage clients towards change. Join us and do extraordinary things. 
 

About Accenture




We work with one shared purpose: to deliver on the promise of technology and human ingenuity. Every day, more than 791,000 of us help our stakeholders continuously reinvent. Together, we drive positive change and deliver value to our clients, partners, shareholders, communities, and each other. We believe that delivering value requires innovation, and innovation thrives in an inclusive and diverse environment. We actively foster a workplace free from bias, where everyone feels a sense of belonging and is respected and empowered to do their best work. At Accenture, we see well-being holistically, supporting our people’s physical, mental, and financial health. We also provide opportunities to keep skills relevant through certifications, learning, and diverse work experiences. We’re proud to be consistently recognized as one of the World’s Best Workplaces™. Join Accenture to work at the heart of change. Visit us at www.accenture.com 




About you:
 

As a Cloud Data Engineer, you will design and maintain data analytic road maps and data structures that support business and technology objectives.  Naturally inquisitive and open to exploration of underlying data, finding valuable insights and work with functional areas to drive identified actions. You enjoy working both freely and as part of a team and have the confidence to influence and communicate with stakeholders at all levels, and to work in a fast-paced complex environment with conflicting priorities.
 

About the role:
 

You will be working on client projects with teams from across our Modern Data Platform and Applied Intelligence practice alongside our industry, functional and technology SMEs on some of our clients most challenging projects. Reporting to the delivery head, you will deliver digestible, contemporary and immediate data content to support and drive business decisions. The key focus of the role is to deliver reports, dashboards and custom solutions for various business critical requirements. You will be involved in all aspects of data engineering from delivery planning, estimating and analysis, all the way through to data architecture and pipeline design, delivery and production implementation.
 

From day one, you will be involved in the design and implementation of complex data solutions ranging from batch to streaming and event-driven architectures, across cloud, on-premise and hybrid client technology landscapes. We are looking for 3+ years of experience in data engineering in a customer or business facing capacity and experience in the following:


To be considered for this role you must have: 
 

-Ability to understand and articulate requirements to technical and non-technical audiences
-Stakeholder management and communication skills, including prioritising, problem solving and interpersonal relationship building
-Strong experience in SDLC delivery, including waterfall, hybrid and Agile methodologies. Experience delivering in an agile environment,
-Experience of implementing and delivering data solutions and pipelines on AWS Cloud Platform.
-A strong understanding of data modelling, data structures, databases, and ETL processes
-An in-depth understanding of large-scale data sets, including both structured and unstructured data
-Strong SQL and/or Python knowledge
-Knowledge and experience of delivering CI/CD and DevOps capabilities in a data environment
 

Location: Melbourne, Sydney, Canberra
